---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Free Savings Goal Calculator — How Long Until You Reach Your Goal?';
const description = 'Enter your savings goal, current balance, and monthly contribution to see exactly when you will reach your target. Free calculator with progress bar and timeline.';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "WebApplication",
      "name": "Savings Goal Calculator",
      "url": "https://gettidyflow.com/tools/savings-goal-calculator",
      "applicationCategory": "FinanceApplication",
      "operatingSystem": "Any",
      "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD" },
      "description": description
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  <section class="tool-hero">
    <div class="tool-hero-inner">
      <span class="tool-badge">Free Tool — No Signup Required</span>
      <h1>Savings Goal <span class="gradient-text">Calculator</span></h1>
      <p class="tool-subtitle">Set a goal, enter what you have today and what you can save each month. We will tell you exactly when you will get there — with a visual timeline to keep you motivated.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tool-app">
    <div class="tool-container">
      <div class="inputs-grid">
        <div class="input-card">
          <label for="goal-amount">Savings Goal</label>
          <div class="input-wrap">
            <span class="symbol">$</span>
            <input type="number" id="goal-amount" placeholder="10,000" min="0" step="100" />
          </div>
          <span class="input-hint">How much do you want to save?</span>
        </div>
        <div class="input-card">
          <label for="current-savings">Current Savings</label>
          <div class="input-wrap">
            <span class="symbol">$</span>
            <input type="number" id="current-savings" placeholder="1,500" min="0" step="100" />
          </div>
          <span class="input-hint">How much have you already saved?</span>
        </div>
        <div class="input-card">
          <label for="monthly-contribution">Monthly Contribution</label>
          <div class="input-wrap">
            <span class="symbol">$</span>
            <input type="number" id="monthly-contribution" placeholder="500" min="0" step="50" />
          </div>
          <span class="input-hint">How much can you save each month?</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="results-section" id="results-section" style="display:none;">
        <div class="progress-card">
          <div class="progress-header">
            <span class="progress-label">Your Progress</span>
            <span class="progress-pct" id="progress-pct">0%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="progress-track">
            <div class="progress-fill" id="progress-fill" style="width:0%"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="progress-amounts">
            <span id="progress-current">$0 saved</span>
            <span id="progress-goal">$0 goal</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="stats-grid">
          <div class="stat-card stat-primary">
            <span class="stat-value" id="stat-months">—</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Months to Goal</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="stat-value" id="stat-date">—</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Target Date</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="stat-value" id="stat-remaining">—</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Remaining to Save</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="timeline-card" id="timeline-card" style="display:none;">
          <h3>Savings Timeline</h3>
          <div class="timeline" id="timeline"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-card" id="tip-card" style="display:none;">
          <span class="tip-icon">💡</span>
          <p id="tip-text"></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="already-done" id="already-done" style="display:none;">
        <div class="done-card">
          <span class="done-icon">🎉</span>
          <h3>You have already reached your goal!</h3>
          <p>Your current savings exceed your goal. Time to set a bigger target or start investing the surplus.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tool-cta">
    <div class="tool-container">
      <div class="cta-card">
        <h2>Track Your Savings Goals Visually</h2>
        <p>This calculator shows you the plan. Our Personal Finance Dashboard helps you <strong>execute it</strong> — track every goal, every account, and every milestone in one beautiful Notion workspace.</p>
        <a href="https://gettidyflow.gumroad.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="cta-button">Get the Personal Finance Dashboard &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="tool-content">
    <div class="tool-container content-narrow">
      <h2>How to Set a Savings Goal That Sticks</h2>
      <p>The biggest reason people fail at saving is vagueness. "I want to save more" does not work. You need a specific number, a deadline, and a plan. This calculator gives you all three.</p>
      <p>Research shows that people who write down specific financial goals are <strong>42% more likely</strong> to achieve them. Pair a clear target with automatic transfers and you are almost guaranteed to succeed.</p>

      <h2>How to Use This Calculator</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Enter your <strong>savings goal</strong> — this could be an emergency fund, vacation, down payment, or anything else.</li>
        <li>Enter your <strong>current savings</strong> — what you have already set aside for this goal.</li>
        <li>Enter your <strong>monthly contribution</strong> — how much you can realistically put away each month.</li>
        <li>The calculator will show your progress, target date, and a visual timeline.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Tips to Reach Your Goal Faster</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Automate transfers</strong> — set up a recurring transfer on payday so saving happens before spending.</li>
        <li><strong>Use a high-yield savings account</strong> — earn 4-5% APY instead of 0.01% at a traditional bank.</li>
        <li><strong>Save windfalls</strong> — tax refunds, bonuses, and gifts can supercharge your progress.</li>
        <li><strong>Cut one expense</strong> — canceling a single $15/month subscription adds $180/year to your goal.</li>
        <li><strong>Track visually</strong> — seeing a <a href="/blog/how-to-track-expenses-in-notion/">progress bar fill up</a> is deeply motivating.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Common Savings Goals and Timelines</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Emergency fund ($10,000)</strong> — saving $500/mo gets you there in 20 months</li>
        <li><strong>Vacation ($3,000)</strong> — saving $250/mo takes 12 months</li>
        <li><strong>Down payment ($50,000)</strong> — saving $1,500/mo takes about 2.8 years</li>
        <li><strong>New car ($25,000)</strong> — saving $800/mo takes about 2.6 years</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Related Resources</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/blog/how-to-save-money-college-student/">How to Save Money as a College Student</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog/why-people-fail-at-budgeting/">Why People Fail at Budgeting (and How to Fix It)</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog/50-30-20-budget-rule-notion/">The 50/30/20 Budget Rule in Notion</a></li>
        <li><a href="/blog/notion-vs-excel-budgeting/">Notion vs Excel for Budgeting</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>Does this calculator account for interest?</summary>
        <p>This calculator shows a simple projection based on fixed monthly contributions. If you are using a high-yield savings account (4-5% APY), you will reach your goal slightly faster than shown. For most short-to-medium term goals (under 3 years), the difference is minor.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What if I cannot save the same amount every month?</summary>
        <p>Use your <strong>average</strong> monthly contribution. Some months you will save more, some less. The timeline will average out. The key is consistency — even small amounts add up over time.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How much should I have in an emergency fund?</summary>
        <p>Most financial advisors recommend <strong>3-6 months of essential expenses</strong>. If you spend $3,000/month on needs, aim for $9,000-$18,000. Start with a $1,000 "starter" emergency fund, then build from there.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Should I save or pay off debt first?</summary>
        <p>Build a small emergency fund first ($1,000), then attack high-interest debt (anything above 7-8%). Once high-interest debt is gone, build your full emergency fund and then save for other goals.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do I stay motivated?</summary>
        <p>Visual tracking is the most effective motivator. Use a <a href="/blog/how-to-track-expenses-in-notion/">Notion dashboard</a> or savings tracker where you can see your progress bar grow. Celebrate milestones — when you hit 25%, 50%, and 75%, reward yourself with something small.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
